9 f. fastidiosam: cloying. — molem propinquam, etc.: thy pile, near neighbor, etc. Cf. 2, 15, 2. The palace called alta domus Epod. 9, 3 which Maecenas built on the Esquiline. It had a lofty tower which commanded a view of the Campagna and sur- rounding hills. From this turris Maecenatiana, as it was later called, Nero is said (Suet. Nero 38) to have watched the burning of Rome.
